# Handy It Out — Cursor Rules

## Project
Handyman service management platform called "Handy It Out". Next.js 14 App Router, MongoDB Atlas, Tailwind CSS, Groq AI, OpenPhone.

## Critical Rules
- JavaScript ONLY. No TypeScript. Use .js and .jsx file extensions.
- AI provider is GROQ (groq.com), NOT Grok (xAI). API URL: https://api.groq.com/openai/v1/chat/completions. Model: llama-3.3-70b-versatile. Env var: GROQ_API_KEY.
- Use 'use client' only on interactive components (forms, filters, modals, anything with useState/useEffect).
- Always populate Mongoose refs (customerId, handymanId) in GET queries.
- Cache MongoDB connection globally in lib/db.js (Vercel serverless requirement).
- Handyman portal must be mobile-first design.
- Normalize phone numbers before customer lookup (strip +1, spaces, dashes, parentheses).
- Hash passwords with bcryptjs (12 salt rounds) via Mongoose pre-save hook.
- NextAuth uses JWT strategy with role and id in session via callbacks.
- All admin API routes must check requireAuth() or requireAdmin().
- The webhook endpoint (/api/webhooks/openphone) does NOT require auth.

## Tech Stack
- Next.js 14 (App Router)
- MongoDB Atlas + Mongoose
- NextAuth.js (CredentialsProvider, JWT)
- Tailwind CSS
- Groq API (llama-3.3-70b-versatile)
- OpenPhone API + Webhooks
- bcryptjs for passwords
- Deployed on Vercel

## File Structure Convention
- Models in /models (PascalCase: User.js, Customer.js, Project.js, Message.js, Quote.js)
- Utilities in /lib (db.js, ai.js, openphone.js, auth.js, messageHandler.js)
- Shared components in /components
- Admin pages under /app/admin/
- Handyman pages under /app/handyman/
- API routes under /app/api/

## Status Enums
- Project: inquiry → quoted → accepted → in_progress → completed → paid
- Message: pending_review → approved → sent → failed → skipped
- Quote: draft → sent → accepted → rejected → revised
- User availability: available | busy | off
- User role: admin | handyman
